abstract: >-
  pdf_signer is a self-contained Rust library and CLI to digitally sign and
  verify PDF documents, implementing the PAdES baseline profiles (ETSI EN 319
  142) from B-B to B-LTA. It performs RFC 5280 path validation (validated
  against the NIST PKITS suite) and authenticated CRL/OCSP revocation checking.
  The cryptography is 100% pure Rust (RustCrypto) — no OpenSSL, no Java, no
  system C libraries — and it powers the pdfsigner (R) and pdfsignerpy (Python)
  bindings.
